Richie Lanz closing magic.

41:15.407 --> 41:17.407
You see, we're, uh...
we're double-booked.

41:17.409 --> 41:19.409
What my partner
is trying to say...

41:19.411 --> 41:21.611
is that we are
tied up here in Kabul.

41:21.613 --> 41:23.246
But we got a shipment
due in Patkia...

41:23.248 --> 41:24.447
Today.
Yep.

41:24.449 --> 41:26.916
Today, Rich. Okay?
It's just a few hours south.

41:26.918 --> 41:29.018
We will send some security
just for show.

41:29.020 --> 41:31.921
Totally not necessary.
This is a sweet Pashtun village.

41:31.923 --> 41:36.926
Rich, these... These are
the very good guys, okay?

41:36.928 --> 41:38.761
All they need is a few thousand rounds
of ammunition...

41:38.763 --> 41:40.830
to defend their village.

41:40.832 --> 41:43.800
We gotta help these guys.
Of course we gotta help these guys.

41:43.802 --> 41:46.302
It's what we do, right?
It's why we're here. Mm-hmm.

41:46.304 --> 41:48.771
It's why we are
all here, okay?

41:48.773 --> 41:51.808
Look, we need somebody
we can trust, all right? An American.

41:51.810 --> 41:53.710
Mm-hmm.
That we can trust.

41:53.712 --> 41:56.980
You drive down, you do the meet and greet,
get paid, obviously, see the sights.

41:56.982 --> 41:59.516
And they're wonderful sights.
The road trip is absolutely incredible.

41:59.518 --> 42:03.019
There's amazing rock formations.
It's like Arizona. Really, really pretty.

42:03.021 --> 42:05.788
And you'll be back at L'Volcan tonight
for cocktail hour.

42:05.790 --> 42:08.350
A tourist trip.
Totally. You got a camera?

42:11.663 --> 42:14.631
Why would I ever do that?

42:14.633 --> 42:17.567
- Love this guy.
- Cool head in a tight spot.

42:17.569 --> 42:20.470
Why would you ever do that?
You think we didn't think about this?

42:20.472 --> 42:22.005
Obviously we did.
We thought about you.

42:22.007 --> 42:23.806
And then we thought about
your current situation.

42:23.808 --> 42:27.076
Look, Rich, the US Embassy,
if pushed, can issue...

42:27.078 --> 42:29.312
what they like to call
a "limited-validity" passport.

42:29.314 --> 42:31.648
Like right now.
<i>Ahora.</i> Right the fuck now.

42:31.650 --> 42:33.883
We can have it
in your hands tonight.

42:33.885 --> 42:35.818
No questions asked.
No.

42:35.820 --> 42:38.321
Like I said, we can and will
make that happen for you.

42:38.323 --> 42:41.758
[ Nick ] Now, it's only good for a year,
but it will get you home.

42:44.396 --> 42:45.995
And it's safe?

42:45.997 --> 42:48.997
[ Sighs ] It's safe as milk.
[ Chuckles ]

42:53.104 --> 42:56.539
[ Brian ] Thirty clicks from our
destination out on the Gardez road.

42:56.541 --> 42:59.242
The mission today is
a simple stop and drop.

43:00.845 --> 43:04.714
We got a Hollywood agent
in the truck with us today.

43:04.716 --> 43:07.150
Let's see if we can't
keep <i> him</i> alive.

43:08.386 --> 43:10.186
You say you're shopping
a book deal.

43:10.188 --> 43:14.257
You happen to be sitting next to
a very well-connected hombre.

43:15.393 --> 43:16.926
Connected to who?

43:16.928 --> 43:20.029
- Danielle Steel.
- Bullshit.

43:20.031 --> 43:22.365
- We dated.
- Get the fuck out of here.

43:22.367 --> 43:24.233
Seriously.
No way.

43:24.235 --> 43:27.870
- Back in the Bay Area.
- You dated Danielle Steel?

43:27.872 --> 43:29.272
Mm-hmm.

43:31.376 --> 43:32.942
You fuck her?

43:34.546 --> 43:36.579
Twice.

43:36.581 --> 43:38.948
[ Brian ]
I read <i> Passion's Promise.</i>

43:40.118 --> 43:42.118
A lot of sex.

43:42.120 --> 43:46.222
- She had beautiful hair, didn't she?
- Back then.

43:46.224 --> 43:49.425
Now I think she's wearing wigs.
And cheap ones. Really.

43:49.427 --> 43:51.394
Like dime-store ones.

43:51.396 --> 43:53.830
[ Brian ]
Synthetic?

43:53.832 --> 43:55.832
[ Richie ] You know, she's got
the money to spend.

43:55.834 --> 43:58.154
I don't know why
she doesn't do it.

44:05.777 --> 44:09.412
- [ Brian ] Come on!
- Mr. Richie! Mr. Richie!

44:09.414 --> 44:10.913
Mr. Richie!

44:10.915 --> 44:13.149
[ Brian ] The fucking truck is on fire.
Get out of there!

44:13.151 --> 44:16.119
Let's go. Get up!
Get up! Let's go.

44:16.121 --> 44:18.788
Get up! Yo, anybody hit?
Anybody hit?

44:18.790 --> 44:23.092
Baba? Get It On John?
Everybody all right?

44:23.094 --> 44:25.495
Where you going?
Mr. Richie! You are blown up?

44:25.497 --> 44:28.164
[ Brian ]
Richie! Where are you going?

44:29.934 --> 44:32.134
- Mr. Richie!
- [ Richie ] Hey!

44:33.038 --> 44:36.372
[ Brian ] The fuck you going?
Get that gear out of the car.

44:37.776 --> 44:39.542
Whoa, Hollywood!
Where are you going?

44:39.544 --> 44:41.177
Hey!

44:42.681 --> 44:45.682
Hey! The fuck you going?

44:56.895 --> 44:59.395
Where are you going?
This wasn't the deal.

45:00.565 --> 45:04.467
What?
[ Coughing, Babbling ]

45:04.469 --> 45:05.968
This wasn't the deal.

45:05.970 --> 45:08.130
The deal was...
[ Sobs ]

45:09.340 --> 45:11.874
The deal was safe as milk.

45:11.876 --> 45:14.143
Was the deal. Safe as milk.

45:14.145 --> 45:16.713
Let's go. Let's go.
Let's get out of here.

45:16.715 --> 45:18.981
Not getting blown to hell.

45:18.983 --> 45:22.985
Milk? Do these look
like milk trucks?

45:22.987 --> 45:25.054
Do I look like a milkman?

45:25.056 --> 45:27.657
I don't like the tone
of your voice.

45:27.659 --> 45:29.692
You're not gonna
get out of here without us.

45:29.694 --> 45:31.728
You're not gonna
get five clicks out of here.

45:32.330 --> 45:34.263
What's a click?

45:34.265 --> 45:36.999
It's a unit of measurement
in the desert.

45:37.001 --> 45:39.502
Mr. Richie... Heads up. Heads up.
What do you got?

45:39.504 --> 45:41.437
Horses. Horses, Mr. Richie.

45:49.080 --> 45:50.747
Oh, fuck.

45:53.885 --> 45:56.319
Come on out. Come on.

46:02.527 --> 46:04.594
We should have taken horses.

46:04.596 --> 46:06.429
[ Men Shouting ]

46:08.700 --> 46:11.300
They are my people. Yes.

46:12.403 --> 46:15.004
It's okay. They're Pashtun.

46:17.375 --> 46:20.943
[ Chattering In Pashto ]

46:23.214 --> 46:24.781
[ Gun Cocks ]

46:25.717 --> 46:28.484
[ Panting ]

46:31.890 --> 46:35.057
Where you goin'?
To close this deal.

46:37.562 --> 46:39.228
Hey.

46:39.230 --> 46:40.897
Richie Lanz.

46:40.899 --> 46:43.432
Talent manager
of Van Nuys, California.

46:43.434 --> 46:45.468
Soon to be in Beverly Hills.

46:45.470 --> 46:47.069
How y'all doing, guys?

46:47.071 --> 46:50.306
<i>As-salaam alaikum.</i>
[ Continues In Pashto ]

46:50.308 --> 46:53.242
[ Speaking Pashto ]

46:53.244 --> 46:55.211
Back at you, babe.

47:10.195 --> 47:11.928
[ Richie ] We got all the stuff
you asked for.

47:11.930 --> 47:14.964
Everything's here.
It's all boxed real nice.

47:14.966 --> 47:16.999
Bows. The whole thing.

47:18.336 --> 47:19.902
[ Speaking Pashto ]

47:20.371 --> 47:21.531
Heads up.

47:24.175 --> 47:26.676
- Yes. He's cool.
- We done, champ?

47:26.678 --> 47:31.347
No, I think... Uh, everything but the,
uh... the money. It's good.

47:31.349 --> 47:34.550
Uh, okay, I guess
you've got what you need.

47:34.552 --> 47:37.553
There's just the matter
of an account balance.

47:53.471 --> 47:55.872
Is he... Is he stiffing me?

48:05.683 --> 48:08.351
He is not on our side.

48:08.353 --> 48:11.433
Yeah, I think I know
a good cop, bad cop when I see it.

48:25.837 --> 48:28.905
He wants to pay you
over tea at his home.

48:31.109 --> 48:33.376
Tea?
Yes. And then dinner.

48:33.378 --> 48:35.444
And then he would like us
to spend the night.

48:35.446 --> 48:38.114
It is an incredible honor,
Mr. Richie.

48:40.618 --> 48:42.218
I don't know.

48:42.220 --> 48:44.720
If you refuse,
he will be honor-bound...

48:44.722 --> 48:46.555
to hunt you down and kill you,

48:46.557 --> 48:50.059
and then hunt down
your family and kill them.

48:50.061 --> 48:51.761
[ Speaking Pashto ]

48:51.763 --> 48:56.599
I'm thinking.
[ Chuckling ]

48:57.902 --> 49:00.036
[ Brian ]
First you lose your girl.

49:00.038 --> 49:02.805
Now you're gonna
lose your head.

49:02.807 --> 49:05.541
You're running out of shit
to lose.

49:05.543 --> 49:08.611
Baba, Johnny,
get this shit off the truck.

49:08.613 --> 49:10.379
Let's get out of here.

49:13.718 --> 49:17.553
<i>[ Richie ] In my country we often say
thank you with a song.</i>

49:17.555 --> 49:20.957
<i>Ready? Ready?
Ready?</i>

49:20.959 --> 49:25.094
♪ Smoke on the water ♪

49:25.096 --> 49:29.565
♪ Fire in the night sky ♪

49:29.567 --> 49:33.069
♪ Smoke on the water ♪

49:33.071 --> 49:38.140
♪ Fire in the sky, yeah ♪

49:38.142 --> 49:43.646
♪♪ [ Instruments Continue ]

49:51.689 --> 49:54.156
Bring it home!

49:54.158 --> 49:58.260
♪ Smoke on the water ♪

49:58.262 --> 50:01.263
♪ Fire in the night ♪

50:01.265 --> 50:06.168
♪ Smoke on the water ♪

50:06.170 --> 50:08.504
♪ Fire in the night ♪

50:08.506 --> 50:10.272
Come on. Bring it down!

50:20.785 --> 50:23.119
♪♪ [ Strumming Continues ]

50:41.172 --> 50:43.172
♪♪ [ Ends ]

50:43.174 --> 50:44.607
Good night, everybody.

50:46.644 --> 50:48.210
Thank you.

50:49.981 --> 50:51.714
Thank you very much.

51:01.692 --> 51:04.493
[ Tariq Speaking Pashto ]

51:04.495 --> 51:06.929
[ Riza Translating ]
"Everything that we have"...

51:06.931 --> 51:10.533
[ Tariq Speaking Pashto ]

51:10.535 --> 51:13.936
"All the wealth of my village,
for what?"

51:13.938 --> 51:16.338
[ Speaking Pashto ]

51:16.340 --> 51:18.774
"To buy more bullets,
more guns."

51:19.877 --> 51:21.710
[ Speaking Pashto ]

51:21.712 --> 51:23.646
"We are surrounded by enemies."

51:24.615 --> 51:26.849
[ Speaking Pashto ]

51:26.851 --> 51:29.118
"The mujahideen warlords."

51:29.854 --> 51:31.854
[ Speaking Pashto ]

51:31.856 --> 51:34.056
"Azam Ghol
is my Pashtun brother."

51:34.058 --> 51:38.928
[ Speaking Pashto ]

51:38.930 --> 51:43.532
"He comes to take my village,
and he wants us to grow the poppy."

51:44.202 --> 51:47.069
[ Speaking Pashto ]

51:47.071 --> 51:49.738
"Twenty-five years of killing."

51:49.740 --> 51:54.376
[ Speaking Pashto ]

51:54.378 --> 51:57.279
"I am tired of war,
and I cannot afford the peace."

52:00.818 --> 52:02.685
[ Speaking Pashto ]

52:06.424 --> 52:08.791
"Allah helps the innocent."

52:10.995 --> 52:12.628
We have a saying:

52:14.999 --> 52:17.733
"The Lord works
in mysterious ways."

52:17.735 --> 52:21.570
[ Riza Speaking Pashto ]

52:27.745 --> 52:29.812
[ Belt Buckle Clinking ]

52:29.814 --> 52:31.380
[ Zipper Opens ]

52:33.851 --> 52:37.319
[ Urinating ]

52:50.468 --> 52:52.001
[ Woman ]
♪ Trouble ♪

52:52.003 --> 52:56.605
♪ Oh, trouble, set me free ♪

52:58.376 --> 53:00.676
[ Zipper Closes ]
♪ I have seen your face ♪

53:00.678 --> 53:04.213
♪ And it's too much,
too much for me ♪

53:07.652 --> 53:09.451
♪ Trouble ♪

53:09.453 --> 53:13.889
♪ Oh, trouble, can't you see? ♪

53:15.126 --> 53:17.459
♪ You're eating my heart away ♪

