53:49.493 --> 53:53.162
♪ So won't you be kind to me? ♪

53:53.164 --> 53:55.831
♪ Just let me go where ♪

53:56.667 --> 53:59.902
♪ I'll have to go there ♪♪

54:26.931 --> 54:29.298
Well, la-di-da.

54:34.438 --> 54:36.719
[ Singsong ]
Taxi.

54:39.744 --> 54:43.879
I heard a girl
singing just now.

54:43.881 --> 54:45.914
Right over there.

54:45.916 --> 54:47.716
A Pashtun girl.

54:47.718 --> 54:49.852
No. Impossible.

54:50.888 --> 54:54.290
The girl in the red burka.
We saw her today.

54:54.292 --> 54:56.058
No, Pashtun women cannot.

54:56.060 --> 54:57.826
They are forbidden to sing.

54:57.828 --> 55:01.797
The chick in the red burka
didn't get the memo.

55:02.733 --> 55:04.667
This girl...

55:05.903 --> 55:09.338
Oh! Oh, God. Oh!

55:09.340 --> 55:11.940
This girl...

55:11.942 --> 55:15.244
Riza, Richie Lanz is about one thing,
one thing only.

55:15.246 --> 55:17.646
What is it?
Your ears.

55:17.648 --> 55:19.048
My ears.

55:20.251 --> 55:22.484
And signing.

55:22.486 --> 55:25.587
So it's two things.
My ears and signing.

55:25.589 --> 55:29.024
I hear 'em, and I sign 'em.

55:29.026 --> 55:30.826
So simple.

55:32.330 --> 55:35.631
A Pashtun woman?
From this village?

55:35.633 --> 55:39.353
They will kill her,
and then right away, they will kill us.

55:39.870 --> 55:44.773
With big, sharp rocks.
That is simple.

55:47.011 --> 55:49.311
Well, I think you're wrong.
I hope you're wrong.

55:49.313 --> 55:51.280
And I think you're wrong.

55:51.282 --> 55:54.116
Look around. Look at that.

55:54.118 --> 55:55.684
Look at that.

55:56.620 --> 55:59.455
Look at that.
Look at all of that.

55:59.457 --> 56:01.623
And look at me.

56:01.625 --> 56:04.059
What the hell am I doing here?

56:05.129 --> 56:07.129
This is so crazy, so random.

56:07.131 --> 56:09.131
This has got to be fate.

56:09.133 --> 56:11.567
There's got to be
a reason for this.

56:11.569 --> 56:14.970
And the reason is that girl...

56:14.972 --> 56:18.073
and that TV show.

56:18.976 --> 56:22.478
I am supposed to be here.

56:23.914 --> 56:27.249
I will talk.

56:27.251 --> 56:30.886
You will translate.

56:30.888 --> 56:33.422
We will die.

56:35.159 --> 56:37.393
That's the spirit.

56:38.896 --> 56:43.499
I see that none of you
are cable or satellite subscribers.

56:44.268 --> 56:46.668
But I'm pretty sure...

56:46.670 --> 56:49.671
you've heard about
<i>Afghan Star,</i> huh?

56:49.673 --> 56:54.176
- [ Riza Translating ]
- It's a big, big hit.

56:54.178 --> 56:55.778
TV show that comes out of Kabul.

56:55.780 --> 56:57.546
[ Rooster Crows ]
[ Goat Bleats ]

56:57.548 --> 56:59.415
Heard about it.
Heard about it.

56:59.417 --> 57:02.084
Well, I happen to have
these babies right here.

57:03.020 --> 57:04.620
[ Translating ]

57:04.622 --> 57:07.456
They're like yours,
but they're magic.

57:07.458 --> 57:10.959
[ Riza Translating ]

57:10.961 --> 57:14.596
And I already know
who the winner is.

57:14.598 --> 57:16.231
[ Riza Translating ]

57:16.233 --> 57:20.769
I know who's the best,
'cause I heard the winner here last night.

57:20.771 --> 57:23.472
In a cave above your village.

57:23.474 --> 57:25.607
[ Riza Translating ]

57:28.312 --> 57:30.946
My all-time guy
would simply tell us,

57:30.948 --> 57:34.616
"Come together, right now,
over her."

57:37.488 --> 57:40.055
[ Shouting In Pashto ]

57:40.057 --> 57:43.559
Uh, she is Tariq's daughter.
She is Tariq's daughter. Of course.

57:43.561 --> 57:45.401
[ Shouting Continues ]
Get out!

57:46.297 --> 57:49.631
He... Is he proud?
He's got to be.

57:50.801 --> 57:53.502
"How dare you
my daughter insult?

57:54.238 --> 57:56.572
Shame. Dishonor.

57:56.574 --> 57:58.540
Eternal death."

57:59.743 --> 58:02.478
I mean, he just goes on, sir.

58:02.480 --> 58:05.614
- [ Chanting In Pashto ]
- [ Others Chanting ]

58:05.616 --> 58:07.449
So I guess that's a "no."

58:07.451 --> 58:09.151
[ Chanting Continues ]

58:19.096 --> 58:20.662
[ Tire Blows ]

58:20.664 --> 58:22.998
Great. A flat tire.

58:23.000 --> 58:24.933
See? We are cursed.

58:24.935 --> 58:28.270
Oh, come on.
It's a flat tire.

58:28.272 --> 58:31.273
I'm sure you know
how to fix it.

58:31.275 --> 58:32.941
[ Engine Stops ]

58:40.451 --> 58:42.317
[ Riza Gasps ]

58:42.319 --> 58:43.952
A ninja!
[ Riza ] Salima.

58:45.556 --> 58:47.823
I must go to Kabul.

58:47.825 --> 58:50.325
Allah gave me this voice.
This is his gift.

58:50.327 --> 58:53.195
Absolutely.

58:53.197 --> 58:55.364
But why are you in my trunk?

58:55.366 --> 58:57.833
I must honor him
with my music.

58:57.835 --> 59:00.235
I must celebrate my God
with my singing.

59:00.237 --> 59:02.404
I must go to Kabul. I must.

59:02.406 --> 59:04.339
Hey, you're preaching
to the choir,

59:04.341 --> 59:08.744
but, you know, your father, family,
apparently will kill me.

59:08.746 --> 59:12.180
Then it is Allah's will,
and we shall die together.

59:12.182 --> 59:14.850
No. No, we shall not.

59:14.852 --> 59:18.554
I have no intention of dying,
ever.

59:19.523 --> 59:21.223
Tell her, Riza.

59:21.225 --> 59:24.059
[ Translating ]

59:28.999 --> 59:31.199
[ Richie ]
Kabul?

59:31.201 --> 59:32.801
That way.

59:38.842 --> 59:41.977
[ Clears Throat ]
Hold it right there, Salima.

59:44.381 --> 59:47.015
From the moment
you heard me sing,

59:47.017 --> 59:48.850
since you found me
in the cave,

59:48.852 --> 59:51.019
since we were put here
on this earth,

59:51.021 --> 59:56.024
everything in our lives
has led us to this time, this place.

59:56.026 --> 59:59.695
Richie Lanz,
our story is already written,

59:59.697 --> 01:00:04.099
and now... now
we shall play our parts.

01:00:04.101 --> 01:00:08.003
We must. There is no choice.
It is God's will.

01:00:13.310 --> 01:00:15.710
Okay, but I'm
gonna want 20%.

01:00:20.117 --> 01:00:22.584
No contract.

01:00:22.586 --> 01:00:25.754
Just a handshake.
That's all I've ever had.

01:00:25.756 --> 01:00:27.956
A handshake is my word.

01:00:30.127 --> 01:00:32.828
Allah loves those
who act justly.

01:00:39.069 --> 01:00:41.803
[ Richie ] All right.
Back in the trunk.

01:00:43.974 --> 01:00:45.641
I'm kidding.

01:00:45.643 --> 01:00:47.409
<i>[ Man ]
♪ People ♪</i>

01:00:47.411 --> 01:00:49.745
<i>♪ Do you understand me now? ♪</i>

01:00:51.148 --> 01:00:54.816
<i>♪ Sometimes I feel
a little mad ♪</i>

01:00:56.587 --> 01:00:58.920
<i>♪ Don't you know no one alive ♪</i>

01:00:58.922 --> 01:01:02.290
<i>♪ Can always be an angel ♪</i>

01:01:02.292 --> 01:01:05.994
<i>♪ When things go wrong,
I seem a little sad ♪</i>

01:01:07.197 --> 01:01:13.368
<i>♪ But I'm just a soul
whose intentions are good ♪</i>

01:01:13.370 --> 01:01:19.341
<i>♪ Oh, Lord, please don't
let me be misunderstood ♪♪</i>

01:01:24.948 --> 01:01:28.216
[ Richie ] A guy wouldn't have
to walk that far.

01:01:30.954 --> 01:01:33.074
[ Riza ]
I must speak.

01:01:33.557 --> 01:01:37.125
Sure. We have time.

01:01:37.127 --> 01:01:41.396
I think you are a smart man,
Mr. Richie, and a good one.

01:01:42.199 --> 01:01:44.399
All right.
Calm down.

01:01:45.335 --> 01:01:48.036
Salima is in danger.

01:01:48.038 --> 01:01:49.571
[ Richie ]
I will protect her.

01:01:49.573 --> 01:01:53.308
[ Riza ] Against millions?
Where will she even sleep?

01:01:53.310 --> 01:01:55.510
I have one bed, one room.

01:01:55.512 --> 01:01:59.314
If I bring an unmarried Pashtun
girl in my building,

01:01:59.316 --> 01:02:01.883
my neighbors would
tear us apart for the sin.

01:02:03.020 --> 01:02:07.489
Do you remember
where we first met?

01:02:07.491 --> 01:02:10.258
[ Chattering ]

01:02:10.260 --> 01:02:11.927
70-30.

01:02:11.929 --> 01:02:14.296
You pay room and board,
all out of pocket.

01:02:17.267 --> 01:02:18.934
Done.

01:02:18.936 --> 01:02:21.670
I also get a taste
of all the merch money.

01:02:21.672 --> 01:02:24.740
And I get a taste
of the merch.

01:02:24.742 --> 01:02:27.142
In all markets,
all endeavors.

01:02:28.278 --> 01:02:30.278
Boys, it's your lucky day.

01:02:30.280 --> 01:02:33.281
All right, none of you are leaving here
with a vicious STD.

01:02:33.283 --> 01:02:37.018
Downside...
Miss Merci's pulling an early retirement.

01:02:37.020 --> 01:02:38.687
Hangin' up my hot pants.

01:02:38.689 --> 01:02:42.357
I suggest you go down to the Chinese
whorehouse on Chicken Street.

01:02:42.359 --> 01:02:44.526
[ Chattering ]

01:02:44.528 --> 01:02:46.795
Breakfast, darlin'?

01:02:46.797 --> 01:02:51.633
Got Captain Crunch,
Lucky Charms.

01:02:51.635 --> 01:02:53.802
I come here for the waitress.

01:02:55.539 --> 01:02:57.272
[ Merci Chuckles ]

01:02:58.876 --> 01:03:00.809
[ Man Speaking Pashto ]

01:03:44.755 --> 01:03:47.856
[ Chanting In Dari ]

01:03:56.800 --> 01:03:59.968
[ Richie ] Scared is normal.
Scared is okay.

01:03:59.970 --> 01:04:03.371
Jon Bon Jovi throws up
before every show.

01:04:03.373 --> 01:04:07.042
[ Riza Speaking Dari ]

01:04:07.044 --> 01:04:09.444
We're on the list.
Lanz, plus one.

01:04:09.446 --> 01:04:11.413
[ Riza Speaking Dari ]

01:04:13.817 --> 01:04:15.383
There is no list.

01:04:17.621 --> 01:04:19.187
There's always a list.

01:04:19.189 --> 01:04:21.790
I appreciate
your passion, but...

01:04:21.792 --> 01:04:24.292
Not my passion.
Salima's passion.

01:04:24.294 --> 01:04:26.161
I mean, I'm just
a hustler from LA.

01:04:26.163 --> 01:04:28.063
You know what's gonna happen
to a Pashtun girl...

01:04:28.065 --> 01:04:30.332
that sings on national TV
in this country?

01:04:30.334 --> 01:04:34.135
What her family is gonna do, her father?
It's already done.

01:04:34.137 --> 01:04:37.172
Just the fact that her coming here,
it's done.

01:04:37.174 --> 01:04:39.708
Look... And yet,
she knows this,

01:04:39.710 --> 01:04:43.245
and here she stands in front of you
just asking for a chance.

01:04:43.247 --> 01:04:45.814
Just asking for you
to give her a chance.

01:04:45.816 --> 01:04:47.515
If the ulema
doesn't shut us down,

01:04:47.517 --> 01:04:50.151
if the ministry of information
doesn't throw me in jail,

01:04:50.153 --> 01:04:52.520
there will be
another season, Mr. Lanz.

01:04:52.522 --> 01:04:56.992
Call me later.
There is no later for Salima, or for you...

01:04:56.994 --> 01:04:59.094
or your country.

01:04:59.096 --> 01:05:03.865
If you let this girl
sing on national TV,

01:05:03.867 --> 01:05:06.868
if you let the Afghan people
see her courage...

01:05:06.870 --> 01:05:09.170
Stop. Stop!
And to hear her voice...

01:05:09.172 --> 01:05:13.275
No! You do not lecture me about courage,
about my country.

01:05:13.277 --> 01:05:15.010
Never. Never.

01:05:15.012 --> 01:05:16.845
Not you. Not an American.

01:05:16.847 --> 01:05:18.346
You people. You talk and talk.

01:05:18.348 --> 01:05:20.882
Have been talking at us
for far too long.

01:05:20.884 --> 01:05:22.517
Courage?

01:05:22.519 --> 01:05:26.521
There are more death threats
on this show than singers.

01:05:26.523 --> 01:05:27.956
Touché.

01:05:27.958 --> 01:05:29.858
Michael Jackson.

01:05:29.860 --> 01:05:33.361
Pink Floyd. The Eagles.

01:05:33.363 --> 01:05:36.531
The Bee Gees.
<i>Saturday Night Fever</i> album.

01:05:36.533 --> 01:05:38.533
Fleetwood Mac.

01:05:38.535 --> 01:05:40.368
Miss Whitney Houston.

01:05:40.370 --> 01:05:43.538
They're all giants.
Demigods.

01:05:43.540 --> 01:05:47.976
They all crushed... crushed
40 million units or more.

01:05:47.978 --> 01:05:49.878
Forty million units.

01:05:49.880 --> 01:05:53.381
Now, you work too hard
for me not to say this.

01:05:53.383 --> 01:05:56.785
I consider you my new friend
in Afghanistan.

01:05:56.787 --> 01:05:59.387
I want you to consider me...

01:06:00.824 --> 01:06:02.657
your new partner.

01:06:04.061 --> 01:06:07.329
Now, I have an 80-20...

01:06:07.331 --> 01:06:10.298
that's been stepped on
by a preexisting 70-30.

01:06:10.300 --> 01:06:13.568
But your 15 against my 85...

01:06:13.570 --> 01:06:15.937
puts us both in a palace
in the hills, my friend.

01:06:15.939 --> 01:06:17.739
And those numbers
can be massaged.

01:06:17.741 --> 01:06:19.474
But the first thing...

01:06:20.844 --> 01:06:23.378
You got to just
hear the girl sing.

01:06:25.916 --> 01:06:28.717
[ Speaking Dari ]

01:06:36.093 --> 01:06:38.126
Richie, the judges
want to know...

01:06:38.128 --> 01:06:39.961
if Salima will be
only singing in English.

01:06:39.963 --> 01:06:41.463
That's never happened before.

01:06:41.465 --> 01:06:45.200
Well, I'm afraid so.
It's a touching story.

01:06:45.202 --> 01:06:47.969
She learned from a seriously
wounded American GI...

01:06:47.971 --> 01:06:49.604
who was trapped in her village.

01:06:49.606 --> 01:06:52.807
As she nursed him back to health,
he taught her one word a day,

01:06:52.809 --> 01:06:55.744
until finally,
the music of the West.

01:06:57.280 --> 01:07:01.783
None of that's true. I mean,
apparently there was a soldier.

01:07:01.785 --> 01:07:03.985
So only Cat Stevens?

01:07:03.987 --> 01:07:05.987
And Jimmy Cliff.

01:07:05.989 --> 01:07:07.989
She does the Muslim West.
That's it.

01:07:07.991 --> 01:07:12.227
<i>♪♪ [ Theme ]</i>

01:07:20.804 --> 01:07:22.704
<i>[ Daoud Speaking Dari ]</i>

01:07:30.647 --> 01:07:33.581
<i>[ Applause ]</i>

01:07:36.053 --> 01:07:37.619
[ Speaking Dari ]

01:07:43.827 --> 01:07:45.493
What?

01:07:46.329 --> 01:07:49.230
What'd that twerp say?
Nothing.

01:07:51.334 --> 01:07:54.002
I'm gonna go kill him, just in case.
No, Richie.

01:07:54.004 --> 01:07:56.871
All right,
when you're done,

01:07:56.873 --> 01:07:59.240
big James Brown finish.

01:07:59.242 --> 01:08:02.377
I come out,
throw a hijab around you,

01:08:02.379 --> 01:08:04.079
escort you off the stage.

01:08:04.081 --> 01:08:05.580
Richie...
You shrug off the shawl,

01:08:05.582 --> 01:08:08.416
stroll back to the mike,
go down, a full knee drop.

01:08:08.418 --> 01:08:11.352
Nail that last verse one last time.
Ignore him. You be you.

01:08:11.354 --> 01:08:15.190
You look like a lady.
You sing like an angel. It'll be enough.

01:08:15.192 --> 01:08:17.425
